cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper proposes a new energy efficient neural network, which is likely to fall under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the classification performance of the proposed network, which suggests that it could fall under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, i.e., cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments on the MNIST dataset also indicate that the proposed network can be used for image classification, which suggests that it could fall under the category of computer vision, i.e., cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper proposes an energy-efficient solution for mobile computing, which suggests that it could fall under the category of systems and control, i.e., cs.SY (Systems and Control).
